Change has been successfully merged
This is from running the tool?
Yeah, I just made the change in update schema script.

I fixed this behavior in the script and rebased this patch on top of the fix.

Done.
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/57407
The new schema pack was causing a really bad diff here.  I've fixed this in the script as well.
wait, should be 2022.2?
Yep.  Fixed the typo.
There's a bug in the script that's causing us to revert to old schema pack versions.  In this case we're going from 1.10.0 to 1.8.1, which probably wasn't intended.  We need to get that sorted out.
Good catch, this should be a blocker to submit this change, right?
It would be, but I now have it fixed.  This patch is now #4 in the series.  Patch #2 fixes this issue.
does this also go backwards?

Yep, DMTF randomized the order of the zip file, which we were relying on.  The new script fixes this.

Marking complete.
With this patch and the one prior, how much binary size are we adding?  Are we going to run some systems out of space?
